# rypuzbench.env — Environment variables for the rypuz benchmark.
#
# Fill in the required values before running the benchmark.
# This file is mounted into each Docker container and sourced by the
# entrypoint.  It must NOT be committed with real credentials.
#
# The benchmark runner (run.py) validates that the required variables
# for the chosen agent are set before launching any containers.

# ── Claude (--agent claude) ─────────────────────────
# See https://code.claude.com/docs/en/env-vars
#  or https://openrouter.ai/docs/cookbook/coding-agents/claude-code-integration

# ── OpenCode ─────────────────────────
# See https://opencode.ai/docs/cli/#environment-variables
#  or https://openrouter.ai/docs/cookbook/coding-agents/opencode-integration

# ── Codex (--agent codex, future) ──────────────────
# See https://developers.openai.com/codex/environment-variables
#  or https://openrouter.ai/docs/cookbook/coding-agents/codex-cli
